#Exercise 2: Simple Sums - 15 Marks
#The first and second variable were both given
num1 = 8 #first variable
num2 = 10 #second variable
#Define a new variable to store the sum of the first two numbers
total = num1 + num2
#Print the value of the sum.
print(f"The total of {num1} and {num2} is {total}.")
#If you want to only see the total then
print(total)
